The paper discusses:
• the historical origin of Fibonacci numbers;
• the Golden Ratio;
• mathematical properties of the sequence;
• applications in nature and art.

3.1 Fibonacci Numbers in Nature
According to the article, Fibonacci numbers appear in many natural phenomena. Examples include:
• sunflower seed arrangements;
• pine cones;
• leaf arrangements (phyllotaxis);
• honeybee genealogy.

